Now come the days of the king.

1857
03:43:34,330 --> 03:43:36,666
May they be blessed.

1858
03:43:56,936 --> 03:43:59,605
This day does not belong to one man...

1859
03:43:59,772 --> 03:44:01,649
...but to all.

1860
03:44:03,317 --> 03:44:06,237
Let us together rebuild this world...

1861
03:44:06,404 --> 03:44:10,658
...that we may share
in the days of peace.

1862
03:44:23,156 --> 03:44:26,156
<font color="#0080C0">Et Eärello</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Out of the Great Sea)</font>

1863
03:44:27,756 --> 03:44:34,156
<font color="#0080C0">Endorenna utúlien.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(to Middle-earth I am come)</font>

1864
03:44:36,156 --> 03:44:40,156
<font color="#0080C0">Sinome maruvan</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(In this place I will abide)</font>

1865
03:44:41,156 --> 03:44:46,656
<font color="#0080C0">ar Hildinyar</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(and my heirs)</font>

1866
03:44:47,656 --> 03:44:56,156
<font color="#0080C0">tenn’ Ambar-metta</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(unto the ending of the world)</font>

1867
03:45:05,156 --> 03:45:06,656
<font color="#008000">Hannon le.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Thank you.)</font>

1868
03:45:19,626 --> 03:45:43,115
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Tinúviel el vanui</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Tinúviel, the elven-fair)</font></i>

1869
03:45:43,626 --> 03:46:02,115
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Elleth alfirin edhelhael</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Immortal maiden elven-wise)</font></i>

1870
03:46:45,146 --> 03:46:47,231
My friends...

1871
03:46:52,528 --> 03:46:55,197
...you bow to no one.

1872
03:47:39,367 --> 03:47:41,494
And thus it was.

1873
03:47:41,660 --> 03:47:45,289
A Fourth Age of Middle-earth began.

1874
03:47:45,456 --> 03:47:48,000
And the Fellowship of the Ring...

1875
03:47:48,167 --> 03:47:52,672
...though eternally bound
by friendship and love...

1876
03:47:52,838 --> 03:47:55,257
...was ended.

1877
03:48:00,262 --> 03:48:05,059
Thirteen months to the day since Gandalf
sent us on our long journey...

1878
03:48:05,226 --> 03:48:09,438
...we found ourselves
looking upon a familiar sight.

1879
03:48:11,982 --> 03:48:14,694
We were home.

1880
03:48:21,242 --> 03:48:23,119
Hi.

1881
03:48:40,302 --> 03:48:42,513
Hey, watch the pumpkin.

1882
03:49:30,603 --> 03:49:32,188
More of the same, Rosie.

1883
03:49:32,355 --> 03:49:34,357
Good night, lads.

1884
03:50:31,914 --> 03:50:35,918
How do you pick up the threads
of an old life?

1885
03:50:37,253 --> 03:50:39,463
How do you go on...

1886
03:50:39,630 --> 03:50:44,844
...when in your heart
you begin to understand...

1887
03:50:46,095 --> 03:50:49,056
...there is no going back?

1888
03:50:49,765 --> 03:50:53,436
There are some things
that time cannot mend...

1889
03:50:53,936 --> 03:50:56,856
...some hurts that go too deep...

1890
03:50:58,607 --> 03:51:01,444
...that have taken hold.

1891
03:51:22,131 --> 03:51:25,176
there and back again...
a hobbit's tale, by Bilbo Baggins

1892
03:51:39,607 --> 03:51:41,484
Mr. Frodo?

1893
03:51:44,820 --> 03:51:46,197
What is it?

1894
03:51:48,032 --> 03:51:51,994
It's been four years to the day
since Weathertop, Sam.

1895
03:51:52,662 --> 03:51:55,373
It's never really healed.

1896
03:51:59,335 --> 03:52:04,590
<i>"There and Back Again: A Hobbit's Tale
by Bilbo Baggins.</i>

1897
03:52:05,341 --> 03:52:09,136
<i>And The Lord of the Rings
by Frodo Baggins."</i>

1898
03:52:09,637 --> 03:52:11,806
You finished it.

1899
03:52:14,684 --> 03:52:16,185
Not quite.

1900
03:52:17,019 --> 03:52:19,563
There's room for a little more.

1901
03:52:22,191 --> 03:52:26,404
Bilbo once told me his part
in this tale would end...

1902
03:52:26,570 --> 03:52:29,865
...that each of us must come and go
in the telling.

1903
03:52:30,741 --> 03:52:33,577
Bilbo's story was now over.

1904
03:52:34,078 --> 03:52:36,998
There would be no more journeys
for him...

1905
03:52:37,164 --> 03:52:38,708
...save one.

1906
03:52:39,458 --> 03:52:43,045
Tell me again, lad,
where are we going?

1907
03:52:43,212 --> 03:52:45,214
To the harbour, Bilbo.

1908
03:52:45,381 --> 03:52:48,092
The Elves have accorded you
a special honour...

1909
03:52:48,259 --> 03:52:50,886
...a place on the last ship
to leave Middle-earth.

1910
03:52:52,596 --> 03:52:54,265
Frodo...

1911
03:52:55,683 --> 03:53:00,229
...any chance of seeing
that old Ring of mine again?

1912
03:53:00,855 --> 03:53:03,107
The one I gave you.

1913
03:53:06,736 --> 03:53:08,904
I'm sorry, Uncle.

1914
03:53:11,449 --> 03:53:14,076
I'm afraid I lost it.

1915
03:53:14,243 --> 03:53:16,037
Oh.

1916
03:53:16,662 --> 03:53:18,122
Pity.

1917
03:53:20,875 --> 03:53:24,754
I should like to have held it
one last time.

1918
03:53:53,908 --> 03:53:58,954
Well, here's a sight
I have never seen before.

1919
03:54:13,135 --> 03:54:16,472
The power of the Three Rings is ended.

1920
03:54:17,264 --> 03:54:20,059
The time has come...

1921
03:54:20,226 --> 03:54:23,521
...for the dominion of Men.

1922
03:54:24,056 --> 03:54:27,056
