1924
03:54:38,244 --> 03:54:42,623
...quite ready
for another adventure.

1925
03:55:13,696 --> 03:55:15,990
Farewell...

1926
03:55:16,157 --> 03:55:18,909
...my brave Hobbits.

1927
03:55:20,870 --> 03:55:22,872
My work is now finished.

1928
03:55:26,792 --> 03:55:31,672
Here at last,
on the shores of the sea...

1929
03:55:32,340 --> 03:55:35,176
...comes the end of our Fellowship.

1930
03:55:38,721 --> 03:55:41,223
I will not say, "Do not weep"...

1931
03:55:41,891 --> 03:55:45,895
...for not all tears are an evil.

1932
03:56:03,454 --> 03:56:05,373
It is time, Frodo.

1933
03:56:10,920 --> 03:56:12,922
What does he mean?

1934
03:56:15,383 --> 03:56:18,260
We set out to save the Shire, Sam.

1935
03:56:19,845 --> 03:56:22,598
And it has been saved.

1936
03:56:26,268 --> 03:56:28,938
But not for me.

1937
03:56:29,855 --> 03:56:32,316
You don't mean that.

1938
03:56:33,526 --> 03:56:35,611
You can't leave.

1939
03:56:44,078 --> 03:56:46,789
The last pages are for you, Sam.

1940
04:00:19,877 --> 04:00:22,755
My dear Sam:

1941
04:00:24,674 --> 04:00:28,010
You cannot always be torn in two.

1942
04:00:28,177 --> 04:00:32,306
You will have to be one and whole
for many years.

1943
04:00:33,057 --> 04:00:38,521
You have so much to enjoy
and to be and to do.

1944
04:00:39,772 --> 04:00:42,942
Your part in the story will go on.

1945
04:00:43,693 --> 04:00:45,444
Well...

1946
04:00:47,321 --> 04:00:49,031
...I'm back.

1947
04:02:31,634 --> 04:02:35,638
<i>Lay down</i>

1948
04:02:37,223 --> 04:02:41,644
<i>Your sweet and weary head</i>

1949
04:02:43,354 --> 04:02:46,941
<i>Night is falling</i>

1950
04:02:47,608 --> 04:02:52,446
<i>You have come
To journey's end</i>

1951
04:02:53,114 --> 04:02:56,867
<i>Sleep now</i>

1952
04:02:57,034 --> 04:03:02,707
<i>And dream
Of the ones who came before</i>

1953
04:03:04,458 --> 04:03:08,379
<i>They are calling</i>

1954
04:03:08,546 --> 04:03:12,675
<i>From across
The distant shore</i>

1955
04:03:14,260 --> 04:03:19,181
<i>Why do you weep?</i>

1956
04:03:19,348 --> 04:03:24,353
<i>What are these tears
Upon your face?</i>

1957
04:03:24,520 --> 04:03:29,567
<i>Soon you will see</i>

1958
04:03:29,734 --> 04:03:34,697
<i>All of your fears
Will pass away</i>

1959
04:03:34,864 --> 04:03:39,952
<i>Safe in my arms</i>

1960
04:03:40,119 --> 04:03:44,623
<i>You're only sleeping</i>

1961
04:03:44,790 --> 04:03:49,795
<i>What can you see</i>

1962
04:03:49,962 --> 04:03:55,217
<i>On the horizon?</i>

1963
04:03:55,384 --> 04:03:59,889
<i>Why do the white gulls</i>

1964
04:04:00,056 --> 04:04:04,769
<i>Call?</i>

1965
04:04:05,936 --> 04:04:10,566
<i>Across the sea</i>

1966
04:04:10,733 --> 04:04:15,988
<i>A pale moon rises</i>

1967
04:04:16,155 --> 04:04:18,866
<i>The ships have come</i>

1968
04:04:19,033 --> 04:04:24,830
<i>To carry you home</i>

1969
04:04:27,083 --> 04:04:31,629
<i>And all will turn</i>

1970
04:04:31,796 --> 04:04:37,134
<i>To silver glass</i>

1971
04:04:37,301 --> 04:04:41,555
<i>A light on the water</i>

1972
04:04:41,722 --> 04:04:47,228
<i>All souls pass</i>

1973
04:04:47,395 --> 04:04:51,607
<i>Hope fades</i>

1974
04:04:53,150 --> 04:04:58,072
<i>Into the world of night</i>

1975
04:04:58,781 --> 04:05:02,618
<i>Through shadows falling</i>

1976
04:05:03,452 --> 04:05:08,582
<i>Out of memory and time</i>

1977
04:05:09,291 --> 04:05:13,004
<i>Don't say</i>

1978
04:05:13,796 --> 04:05:18,801
<i>We have come now to the end</i>

1979
04:05:19,635 --> 04:05:24,056
<i>White shores are calling</i>

1980
04:05:24,223 --> 04:05:27,768
<i>You and I will meet again</i>

1981
04:05:27,935 --> 04:05:34,400
<i>And you'll be here
In my arms</i>

1982
04:05:35,609 --> 04:05:39,697
<i>Just sleeping</i>

1983
04:05:39,864 --> 04:05:44,702
<i>What can you see</i>

1984
04:05:44,869 --> 04:05:49,832
<i>On the horizon?</i>

1985
04:05:49,999 --> 04:05:54,795
<i>Why do the white gulls</i>

1986
04:05:54,962 --> 04:06:00,384
<i>Call?</i>

1987
04:06:00,551 --> 04:06:05,639
<i>Across the sea</i>

1988
04:06:05,806 --> 04:06:10,811
<i>A pale moon rises</i>

1989
04:06:10,978 --> 04:06:13,773
<i>The ships have come</i>

1990
04:06:13,939 --> 04:06:20,279
<i>To carry you home</i>

1991
04:06:21,489 --> 04:06:26,619
<i>And all will turn</i>

1992
04:06:27,203 --> 04:06:32,041
<i>To silver glass</i>

1993
04:06:32,208 --> 04:06:36,337
<i>A light on the water</i>

1994
04:06:36,504 --> 04:06:40,383
<i>Grey ships pass</i>

1995
04:06:40,549 --> 04:06:46,222
<i>Into the West</i>

